//Others Ingredients: How to cook:
//Adobo
2 tbsp. vegetable oil 
 1/3 pound chicken 
 1 large onion 
 2 tbsp. minced garlic 
 1/3 cup white vinegar 
 2/3 cup soy sauce 
 2 tsp. black pepper 
 1 bay leaf
1. Heat the vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. 
 2. Cook chicken pieces until golden brown on both sides, then remove. 
 3. Stir in the onion and garlic; cook until they soften and brown, about 6 minutes. 
 4. Pour in vinegar and soy sauce, and season with garlic powder, black pepper, and bay leaf. 
 5. Add the browned chicken, increase the heat to high, and bring to a boil. 
 6. Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until the chicken is tender and cooked through. 
 //Omelet
2 large eggs 
 Olive oil 
 10g cheddar cheese 

1. Crack the eggs into a mixing bowl, season with a pinch of salt and black pepper, then beat well with a fork until fully combined. 
 2. Place a small non-stick frying pan on a low heat to warm up. 
 3. Grate the cheese onto a board and set aside. 
 4. Add 1/2 tbsp. of oil to the hot pan, then carefully pour in the eggs. 
 5. Tilt the pan to spread them out evenly, using a fork to swirl the eggs around the pan a little. 
 6. When the omelet begins to cook and firm up, but still has a raw egg on top, sprinkle over the cheese. 
 7. Using a spatula, ease around the edges of the omelet, then fold it over in half. 
 8. When it starts to turn golden brown underneath, remove the pan from the heat and slide the omelet onto a plate. 

//Sinigang
500g pork, sinigang cut 
 Water 
 1 med. tomatoes, quartered 
 1 sm. onion, quartered 
 1 cup taro root, cubed 
 3-4 tbsp. sinigang na gabi mix 
 1 pc. siling haba 
 1-2 tbsp. fish sauce 
 1/2 cup sitaw 
 2 cups kangkong 

1. Place the tomatoes, pork, and onions in a pot with enough water to cover pork, bring to a boil then lower heat to simmer for 1 1/2 hours until pork is tender. 
 2. Skin top from time to time to get rid of impurities. 
 3. After 30 mins. of cooking pork, add gabi cubes. 
 4. Once pork is tender, add sinigang mix, siling haba, and simmer for 5 mins. 
 5. Add the sitaw then simmer for another 5 mins. 
 6. Season to taste with patis then add kangkong leaves and simmer for 2-3 mins. Adjust seasoning according to taste. Serve while hot.
//Giniling
2 tbsp. oil 
 1 tbsp. garlc, minced 
 1 med. onion, chopped 
 2 pcs. tomatoes, chopped 
 1/2 kilo ground pork 
 1 1/2 cups of water 
 2 med. potatoes, diced 
 2 med. carrot, diced 
 1/2 cup green peas 
 1/2 cup tomato sauce
1. In a large pan, heat oil and saute garlic, onion, and tomatoes for a few minutes. 
 2. Add ground pork then stir. 
 3. Pour in water and cook for 20 mins. 
 4. Add potatoes and carrots then cook for 5 mins. 
 5. Add peas then stir in tomato sauce. 
 6. Season with salt and pepper and let simmer for 5 mins.
//Tinola
1 tbsp. oil 
 1 sm. onion, sliced thinly 
 2-3 cloves garlic, minced 
 2 thumb-sized ginger, julienned 
 1 whole chicken, cut into serving pieces 
 2 tbsp. fish sauce 
 5 cups water 
 1 sm. green papaya, wedged 
 1 bunch kangkong 

1. In a pot, over medium heat, heat oil. 
 2. Add onions and garlic and cook until limp and aromatic. 
 3. Add chicken and cook for about 5-7 mins. or until it changes color. 
 4. Add fish sauce and cook for about 1-2 mins. 
 5. Add more water and bring to a boil skimming scum that floats on top. 
 6. Lower heat, cover and simmer for about 30-35 mins. 
 7. Add papaya and cook for about 3-5 mins. Season with salt and pepper to taste. 8. Add kangkong and cook until wilted. Serve while hot.
